<h2 style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Number Line</h2>

<div style="line-height:2">
<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">The Number Line 1 to 20 helps the children to visualize the sequence and pattern of number. The numbers are arranged from the smallest to the greatest on the number line.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Click the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_visibility.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button to use the Patch pointer<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/icon_numberline_patch.png" style="vertical-align:middle">or the red pointer<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/icon_numberline_dot.png" style="vertical-align:middle">. The pointers can help the children understand that the smaller numbers are toward the left and the greater numbers are toward the right.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Children can also perform addition and subtraction with the Number Line. To demonstrate the addition of 5 plus 3, first move the red dot to 5, then click the + button for three times to add 3. The arrow will appear to indicate the three steps forward. The arrow now is pointing at 8, therefore 5+3=8. Same process applies to subtraction. For subtraction, the pointer will move backward.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Number Line helps the children to visualize the changes of numbers when we add and subtract. When we add, the number is getting bigger; therefore, it is moving to the right. It moves to the left when we subtract, thus, it is getting smaller.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">To write any numbers, use the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_pencil.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button. Double-click on the button to change the colours of the pencil. Use the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_eraser.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">or<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_clear.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button to remove all the scribbles with the pencil tool. To start counting a new set of numbers, click the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_reset.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button.</p>
</div>